title: For Sale/Trade:  Hi Point 4095TS
postcontent:
As the title says I have a practically new Hi Point 4095TS carbine that I'd be interested in trading or selling.

I just bought this last week and it is essentially new, only put 80 rounds through it. title: For Sale:  Bulgarian AK-74, not Century! 5.45x39, original barrel, matching parts, Nodak receiver, true brake, four mags, leather sling
postcontent:
I've decided I'm going to concentrate on AR-15s so I'm selling my AK-74. This gun is an original Circle-10 Bulgarian military kit built on a Nodak NDS-2 receiver, NOT a Century build that uses a non-chromed US-made barrel that's vulnerable to the corrosive primers of surplus. The Circle-10 armory is famous for quality and still operates today as the privatized company Arsenal Inc. Unlike many cheaper Century AK-74s rifle that use a less-effective clone with fewer features and thus less recoil reduction this also has a true 74 brake with expansion chambers, chamber vents, and top/left ports. Barrel is original military surplus and includes chrome lining for corrosion and fouling resistance.

The kit the gun was built on appears to be serialized and all-matching. The serial matches on the bolt, extractor, bolt carrier, dust cover, and front trunnion (according to the AKFiles forum there are surprisingly no serials on Bulgarian surplus barrels, only journal size numbers for final assembly.)

Comes with four mags, three of them appear to be plum Russian Tula mags (all have sanitized markings on at least one side and one has been painted black) while the fourth is a newer Promag. Also comes with a sturdy surplus leather sling. I have 10 more mags available (sanitized and marked Tula, Bulgarian surplus in various colors, and one steel Romanian) if you're interested in them, but I need to sit down and figure out the current market value first.

As you can see in the pictures below I've taken extreme care to keep it clean after firing surplus, there is no visible rust or pitting anywhere that I could see on the gun. As is the case on these surplus Bulgarian kits (and other guns that use it today like Saigas) the enamel paint they used as finish shows some wear on some of the sharp edges of the gun, in the normal places they tend to occur. There are also some marks on the gas block and front sight block that appear to have been made by the jaws of a vise, not sure where they came from as they were there when I received the gun. They're a little unsightly upon close inspection but are purely cosmetic, if you ever refinished the gun they could be smoothed out with a minimal efforts from a file or small disc sander and should blend into the new finish well. Front sight looks to be nice and straight, no tilting like is common on AKs like the SAR or WASR series while the actual bore is bright and shiny. Reliability has been flawless for me with this gun so far, as it should since it was a complete de-milled gun that was simply placed in a new semiauto-only receiver. 

Here's an imgur album I created which contains higher-resolution zoomable versions of the pictures I uploaded to Armslist, along with additional pictures of the internals and barrel to show they're rust-free. Sorry about the carbon buildup on the piston- I didn't remember to scrape it off when I cleaned the gun for pics but it is NOT corrosion:

http://imgur.com/a/qrg6h

Considering this gun but don't have any ammo for it? I have 3180 rounds of Russian surplus 7n6 ammo for sale at a price you won't beat locally or even online: 

http://www.armslist.com/posts/2830224/st-louis-missouri-ammo-for-sale--3180-rounds-of-russian-7n6-5-45x39mm-ammo--for-ak-74--vepr--saiga--wasr-2--etc---will-divide-lot

I live about 40 miles north of St. Louis and if you're coming from the city I would be willing to drive as far as St. Charles county to meet up at a gun-friendly public place, such as Bass Pro or Cabelas.

title: For Sale:  CZ P07 in 9mm
postcontent:
If you like the DA/SA platform and looking for a new carry gun this is the gun for you! Roughly the size of the Glock 19 this gun fits 16 rounds of 9mm into the mag giving it total capacity of 17 rounds. It features CZ's omega trigger system allowing you to switch between a deckocker or a safety to carry cocked and locked, both ambidextrous. It's a very soft shooter thanks to its low bore axis and has a very smooth double action pull for an accurate first shot and light single action pull for on point subsequent shots. Comes with everything from the factory (2 mags, case, paperwork, etc). This gun was carried and does show minor holster wear but is functionally perfect. Estimated round count: 400 rounds.

Will temporarily be in Sunrise for the weekend (leaving Sunday). Not too familiar with the area so my driving will be very limited.
Not taking trades at this time.
